    url: 'http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Anton_Wilson',
    text: 'Robert Anton Wilson (born Robert Edward Wilson; January 18, 1932 \u2013 January 11, 2007) was an American author, futurist, and self-described agnostic mystic. Recognized within Discordianism as a Episkopos, pope and saint, Wilson helped publicize Discordianism through his writings and interviews.Wilson described his work as an \\attempt to break down conditioned associations, to look at the world in a new way, with many models recognized as models or maps, and no one model elevated to the truth\\". His goal was \\"to try to get people into a state of generalized agnosticism, not agnosticism about God alone but agnosticism about everything.\\"Following a career in journalism and as an editor, notably for Playboy, Wilson emerged as a major countercultural figure in the mid-1970s, comparable to one of his coauthors, Timothy Leary, as well as Terence McKenna."',
